aspace_helpers.title: Generating MARC records from C0140 EAD component records/archival objects in Resource records

comments.body:
Hi @regineheberlein - Thanks for your work on this. I was able to review some records and noticed just a couple of issues:

1. For format, the records note: "Manuscript, Book." Examples: C0140_c00001 and C0140_c03358
2. This is fairly minor, but is there a way to add a comma between the title and the date of creation? It's confusing when creator life dates are included in the title in particular. Examples: C0140_c00001 and C0140_c03358.

Of more concern is the missing processinfo note, though Kelly mentioned that you created a ticket to index these. Is that correct?

Thanks @faithc ! 
The format display is correct, even though it is confusing. I had to ask DT about it myself. It's the display for resources coded as mixed materials.

I'm afraid adding a comma after the title is out of scope for this project--that would be a ticket in orangelight, which handles the display. 

You are correct: the processinfo note is being investigated on a separate ticket. https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/issues/1977

Ah ok, gotcha re: the format display and title punctuation. 

And great; thanks re: processinfo.

From my quick chat with Kelly, it seems like we should also create a ticket so that viaf names and non-LC SH, like those from the Homosaurus, are indexed and discoverable?

Yup, you could open one in bibdata if you want to request additional authorities to be indexed: https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata

That would be a new feature, so I'll leave it to you to request it.

pulfalight.title: Add location info in addition to repository -- for some users, location is more important than repository

comments.body:
### Summary
Location information is missing from results in the search result set. Location information is valuable to many people. 

### Impact 
The user may need to walk to another location for relevant material. (@ccleeton is this how the lack of location info affects patrons?)

### Priority recommendation

- [ ] asap
- [ ] within the next 3 weeks
- [x] PO will prioritize

## Sudden Priority Justification
_Required if "asap" or "within the next 3 weeks" is checked. Add "Sudden Priority" and "Maintenance/Research" labels_

### Expected behaviour
Each record should have a location. One place to put this is preceding the repository name in the record breadcrumbs.

### Actual behaviour
No location information is displayed yet for any record. 

### Steps to reproduce behaviour
[See highlight reel.](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1-TNPg3_kRlsyk3lUEzTlmRFlJRvsCegd/view?usp=sharing)

### Example
See highlight reel.

### Context
This issue is the result of a UX research session. The bug was reported during a usability test conducted by the Pulfalight Operations Group in April of 2022.
